    <fr:title text="-Algebra"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
    <fr:date>
      <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
      <fr:month>5</fr:month>
      <fr:day>27</fr:day>
    </fr:date>
    <fr:authors />
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <fr:p>In mathematical analysis and in probability theory, a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra is part of the formalism for defining sets that can be measured (<fr:link type="local" href="FA-003C.xml" addr="FA-003C" title="Measurable Set">measurable sets</fr:link>)</fr:p>
    <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be some set, and let  <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P(X)]]></fr:tex> represent its power set, the set of all subsets of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex></fr:p>
    <fr:p>Then a subset <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma  \subseteq  P(X)]]></fr:tex> is called a <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra if and only if it satisfies the following three properties:</fr:p>
    <fr:ol><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex> is closed under complementation</fr:li>
  <fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex> is closed under countable union</fr:li></fr:ol>
    <fr:p>From these properties, it follows that the <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra is also closed under countable intersections (by applying De Morgan's laws).</fr:p>
    <fr:p>It also follows that the empty set is also in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex>, because from <fr:strong>(1)</fr:strong>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex> and from <fr:strong>(2)</fr:strong>, the complement of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex>, the empty set, is also in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Sigma ]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
    <fr:p>Notice that the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\left \{ X, \emptyset  \right \}]]></fr:tex> satisfies all 3 of the properties, making it the smallest possible <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\sigma ]]></fr:tex>-algebra</fr:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
